2 Synthetic Control

2.1 Transform data

period <- 
    seq(
      1961, 
      1969, 
      2
    )
df <-
  Synth::dataprep(
    foo = basque,
    predictors = 
      c(
        "school.illit", 
        "school.prim", 
        "school.med", 
        "school.high", 
        "school.post.high", 
        "invest"
      ),
    predictors.op = "mean",
    time.predictors.prior = 1964:1969,
    special.predictors = 
      list(
        list(
          "gdpcap", 
          1960:1969, 
          "mean"
        ), 
        list(
          "sec.agriculture", 
          period, 
          "mean"
        ), 
        list(
          "sec.energy", 
          period, 
          "mean"
        ),
      list(
        "sec.industry", 
        period, 
        "mean"
      ), 
      list(
        "sec.construction", 
        period, 
        "mean"
      ), 
      list(
        "sec.services.venta", 
        period, 
        "mean"
      ),
      list(
        "sec.services.nonventa", 
        period, 
        "mean"
      ), 
      list(
        "popdens", 
        1969, 
        "mean"
      )
    ),
    dependent = "gdpcap", 
    unit.variable = "regionno", 
    unit.names.variable = "regionname", 
    time.variable = "year",
    treatment.identifier = 17, 
    controls.identifier = c(2:16, 18), 
    time.optimize.ssr = 1960:1969, 
    time.plot = 1955:1997
  )

2.2 Compute the weights

result <- 
  Synth::synth(
    data.prep.obj = df,
    method = "BFGS"
  )

2.4 Plot the outcomes of treated and synthetic control

Synth::path.plot(
  synth.res = result, 
  dataprep.res = df, 
  Ylab = "real per-capita GDP (1986 USD, thousand",
  Xlab = "year", 
  Ylim = 
    c(
      0, 
      12
    ), 
  Legend = 
    c(
      "Basque country", 
      "Synthetic Basque country"
    ),
  Legend.position = "bottomright"
)

2.5 Plot the gaps

Synth::gaps.plot(
  synth.res = result, 
  dataprep.res = df, 
  Ylab = "real per-capita GDP (1986 USD, thousand)",
  Xlab = "year", 
  Ylim = 
    c(
      -1.5, 
      1.5
    ), 
  Main = NA
)

3 Synthetic DID

3.1 Transform data

df <-
  california_prop99 %>%
  synthdid::panel.matrices(
    unit = "State", 
    time = "Year", 
    outcome = "PacksPerCapita", 
    treatment = "treated"
  )
names(df)
## [1] "Y"  "N0" "T0" "W"

3.2 DID: estimate

result_did <- 
  synthdid::did_estimate(
    Y = df$Y, 
    N0 = df$N0, 
    T0 = df$T0
  )
plot(result_did)

result_did
## synthdid: -27.349 +- NA. Effective N0/N0 = 38.0/38~1.0. Effective T0/T0 = 19.0/19~1.0. N1,T1 = 1,12.
vcov(
  result_did,
  method = "placebo"
) %>%
sqrt()
##          [,1]
## [1,] 14.31961

3.3 DID: weight

synthdid::synthdid_units_plot(
  result_did
)
